{"search_data": "KeralaKerala Sarathi Scheme \u2013 Govt. to Roll-Out Unified Licence Scheme by 31 December Kerala govt. to roll out Sarathi scheme to unify licensing by 31 December 2018 as proposed previously by the Union Ministry of Road Transport & Highways, applicants to get new smart card driving licencesKerala Sarathi Scheme for Unified LicensingSarathi scheme aims to issue smart card driving licences to drivers. These smart cards will have a number of security features which includes QR code and hologram. Each of the district office in the state of Kerala issues around 40,000 licences (on an average) every year. Now all the new applicants would be given these smart cards with more security features.The plan is to bring uniformity in the design of licence issued across the state. For this purpose, the state govt. is planning a centralised printing system to ensure the uniformity in the design of the licences. The design of the new licence is going to be finalised soon.All the new applicants would get high quality smart cards which are going to more durable (more resistant to wear and tear) than the current paper licences. Even all the existing licence holders would get new smart driving licences when they come for renewal.Kerala New Smart Card Driving LicenceThe VAHAN & SARATHI schemes are conceptualized in such a way which to enable them to capture the functionalities as mandated by Central Motor Vehicle Act, 1988 as well as State motor vehicle rules. These schemes would be implemented in a customized manner in the core product to suit the requirements of 29 states & 7 union territories of India.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}